The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 14 April is 41,582 (4,812.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 09 April, there were 129 new confirmed cases (14.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 02 April, there were 155 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 17% (26 fewer cases).
